The paper deals with image super-resolution using a generative adversarial network (GAN), which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a GAN also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a deep residual network, which is commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
